name: Buffalo-Ft. Erie Enrollment Center
directions:
The first step in the process is the Canadian interview, IN CANADA (your appointment time), and the second step in the process is the United States interview, IN THE UNITED STATES.  YOU HAVE TO COMPLETE BOTH THE CANADIAN AND UNITED STATES INTERVIEWS TO COMPLETE THE INTERVIEW PROCESS!!

	Location of the Canadian interview (THE FIRST STEP):
		10 Central Ave
		Ft. Erie, Ontario, Canada L2A 3S6

Directions to Ft. Erie location: Physically located on the Canadian side of the Peace Bridge which connects Buffalo, NY and Ft. Erie, ON.
From Canada – QEW to Ft. Erie, ON – Central Ave exit. Right at the traffic light.  Left into the parking lot on Central Ave.  Follow signs marked “Enrollment Centre” to enter the building.  Entrance is on the Central Ave and Garrison Rd intersection.
From USA – Peace Bridge to Ft. Erie, ON – Central Ave exit (after toll). Right at the stop sign.  Left into the parking lot on Central Ave.  Follow signs marked “Enrollment Centre” to enter the building.  Entrance is on the Central Ave and Garrison Rd intersection.

	Location of the United States interview (THE SECOND STEP):
		 1 Peace Bridge Plaza
		Buffalo, New York 14213
	
Directions to Buffalo location:  Physically located on the United States side of the Peace
Bridge which connects Buffalo, NY and Ft. Erie, ON.
From Canada (every applicant will be arriving from Canada) – Peace Bridge to Buffalo, NY.  After completing immigration/customs inspection, park in the designated location and enter the Peace Bridge Cargo Facility/Warehouse by using the double glass doors at the top of the stairs at the main entrance to the right of the cargo bays/docks.  Take the first hallway on the right and enter Room 145.  Please take a seat wait patiently.
notes:
**OPEN with new two-step interview process; PLEASE READ CAREFULLY!!**
CHECKLIST BEFORE ARRIVAL:
•	Bring physical printout of appointment confirmation – NO digital/phone copies!
•	Arrive in Canada for Canadian interview FIRST (THIS IS YOUR APPOINTMENT TIME)
•	After Canadian interview, return to the United States for the United States interview SECOND

1) You must bring a physical printout of your appointment confirmation. 2) You MUST bring proof of citizenship (NO COPIES) to your interview. 3) You must schedule an appointment for each applicant in your family or domicile. If there are not enough appointments available on a particular day to accommodate the members of your family, you must select another day. Appointments are not required to be in sequential time slots as you may all arrive at any one of the appointment times. 4) If you have ever been arrested, you must bring original court documentation for each arrest that clearly identifies the charge and disposition of each charge. 5) Applicants who require a visa must provide a valid I-94 at the time of the interview.  This includes those participating in the Visa Waiver Program. 6) Children under 18 must be accompanied by a parent or guardian. NOTE: If the interview is for a child under the age of 18 AND the child does not reside with both parents or legal guardians, the non-attending parent or legal guardian must sign a letter of consent agreeing to the minor’s enrollment in the Trusted Traveler Program. To expedite the process, please email BuffaloTTP@cbp.dhs.gov and input "Letter of Consent" into the subject line to obtain an advanced copy. In cases of sole custody or if only one parent is recorded on the minor's birth certificate, the parent or legal guardian does not require a consent letter but must provide proof of sole custody agreement or long form birth certificate.

name: Ottawa International Airport
directions:
The NEXUS Enrolment Centre is located in the Ottawa Macdonald-Cartier International Airport on the Arrivals Level. Take North entrance to Terminal. Once inside, turn right and the NEXUS office is on the left just before the OPERATIONS/Ottawa Police double doors.


Le centre d’inscription est situé à l’aéroport international Macdonald-Cartier d’Ottawa au niveau des arrivées.  Prendre l'entrée nord vers le Terminal. Une fois à l'intérieur, tournez à droite et le bureau NEXUS est sur la gauche juste avant les doubles portes OPÉRATIONS/Police d'Ottawa.
notes:
You booked a two-step interview which requires a Canadian interview and a second separate US interview. Canada Border Services Agency (CBSA) officers will complete the Canadian portion of the NEXUS interview at a Canadian airport enrolment centre. U.S. Customs and Border Protection (CBP) will conduct the U.S. portion of the interview at a Canadian airport preclearance location. 
To access a preclearance location at an airport for your U.S. interview, you must be a ticketed passenger travelling to the U.S. that day. No appointment is required for this U.S. interview but you should give yourself extra time before your flight. 
For more information on the two-step interview process: NEXUS enrolment centres (cbsa-asfc.gc.ca)
For account related questions, contact the CBP Information Center: https://help.cbp.gov. 
Instructions spéciales à l’intention des demandeurs
Vous avez pris rendez-vous pour une entrevue en deux étapes, composée d’une entrevue canadienne, suivie d’une entrevue distincte des États-Unis (É.-U.). Des agents de l’Agence des services frontaliers du Canada (ASFC) effectueront la partie canadienne de l’entrevue dans un centre d’inscription d’un aéroport canadien. Le Service des douanes et de la protection des frontières (SDPF) des États-Unis effectueront l’entrevue des É.-U. dans une zone de précontrôle d’un aéroport canadien. 
Pour accéder à un lieu de précontrôle dans un aéroport pour votre entrevue avec les États-Unis, vous devez avoir un billet pour vous rendre aux États-Unis ce jour-là. Aucun rendez-vous n’est nécessaire pour l’entrevue des É.-U., mais vous devez prévoir plus de temps avant votre vol.
Pour plus de renseignements sur le processus d’entrevue à deux étapes : Centres d'inscription NEXUS (cbsa-asfc.gc.ca)
Si vous avez des questions à propos de votre compte, veuillez communiquer avec le centre d’information du SDPF : https://help.cbp.gov.

directions:
The Niagara Falls EC is located at 2250 Whirlpool Street, Niagara Falls, NY.  The EC is located adjacent to the U.S. side of the Whirlpool Bridge in Niagara Falls.  

****Do NOT enter the U.S. at the Whirlpool Bridge unless you are a current NEXUS or Global Entry member in possession of a valid card.**********  If you or a passenger in your vehicle do not have valid NEXUS or Global Entry cards, you may instead enter the U.S. at the Rainbow, Lewiston/Queenston, or Peace Bridges.
notes:
1)	Only those with scheduled appointments will be allowed to enter the enrollment center.
2)	You MUST bring proof of citizenship (NO COPIES) with you to your interview. For Global Entry applicants this MUST be a valid passport. 
3)	You must schedule an appointment for each applicant in your family or domicile. If there are not enough appointments available on a particular day to accommodate the members of your family, then you must select another day. Appointments are not required to be in sequential time slots, you may come in at any one of the appointment times.   
4)	If ever arrested, you must bring original court documentation for each arrest that clearly shows the charge and disposition of each charge. 
5)	Applicants who require a visa must provide a valid I-94 at the time of interview, this includes those participating in the Visa Waiver Program. 
6)	Children under 18 must be accompanied by a parent or guardian.  

NOTE:  If the interview is for a child under the age of 18 AND the child does not reside with both parents or legal guardians; then the other parent or legal guardian must sign a letter of consent agreeing to the minor’s enrollment in the Trusted Traveler Program.  To expedite the interview process, please email BuffaloTTP@cbp.dhs.gov and input "Letter of Consent" into the subject line to obtain a copy of this consent in advance.  In cases of sole custody or if only one parent is recorded on the minor's birth certificate, the parent or legal guardian does not require a consent letter but must provide proof of sole custody agreement or long form birth certificate.

notes:
Instructions for your scheduled NEXUS/FAST interview at the Derby Line Enrollment Center (EC)
The United States Customs and Border Protection and the Canada Border Services Agency (CBSA) have implemented a new interview process at the NEXUS Enrollment Center located at Derby Line, VT.  The interview will be a split process where the 1st portion of the interview will be conducted at the Derby Line EC in the United States and the second portion will take place directly across the international border at the Stanstead port of entry in Canada.  
In order to complete the process for your enrollment in the program following your interview at the Derby Line EC you must immediately report to the CBSA Port of Entry on Route 55 in Stanstead, Quebec and complete your interview with CBSA personnel.  To get to the Stanstead office (Rte 55), just take Interstate 91 north.  Advise the CBSA officer that you are here to complete the 2nd portion of your NEXUS interview.  Failure to report to CBSA and complete the interview process will result in exclusion from the program.
**********************
Instructions pour votre entrevue NEXUS/EXPRES prévue au centre d’inscription (CI) de Derby Line

name: Champlain Global Entry Enrollment Center
directions:
From Albany by Car: Head North on I-87. Get off at Exit 43 (last US exit before entering Canada) at the end of the off ramp you will come to a T intersection, make a right onto the East service road. Follow the East service road approximately 1/4 of a mile & make a right under the interstate. Follow West Service Road (North) until you reach the CBP parking lot. Park your car and walk to the big gray building with the word CHAMPLAIN written on it. Go  through the door  located beneath the first "A" in CHAMPLAIN.
From Montreal by Car: Head south on Auto Route 15 to the US Border. Complete Inspection process to enter the US. Head south on I-87. Get off at Exit 43. At the end of the off ramp, make a right. Head North on West Service Road. The West Service Road ends in the CBP parking lot.  Park your car and walk to the big gray building with the word CHAMPLAIN written on it. Go  through the door  located beneath the first "A" in CHAMPLAIN.
From Albany by Commercial Truck: Head North on I-87.  Get off at Exit 43 (last US exit before entering Canada) at the end of the off ramp you will come to a T intersection, make a right onto the East service road. Follow the East service road approximately 1/4 of a mile and make a right under the interstate. Follow West Service Road (North). Park your Truck in the Peterbilt Truck stop parking lot & walk up the service road to the CBP parking lot.
From Montreal by Commercial Truck: Head south on Auto Route 15 to the US Border. Complete Inspection process, to enter the US, Clear your shipment & advise the Officer that you also have a FAST appointment. If empty or Bob-Tail, Complete Inspection process to enter the US & advise the Officer that you have a FAST appt. Before you continue South on I-87, make a sharp right & pull into the Cargo parking lot.
After parking in the parking lot:  Walk to the Cargo Building, Go through the Glass sliding doors & make your first left.
notes: Please remember to bring your conditionally approved letter, proof of all Citizenships (ie: all  Passports, birth certificates (especially for minors)), proof of status (ie: work permit, Legal permament resident card), drivers license, orginial copies of Criminal records and Pardon paperwork. Iris Scan is available at this location.

name: DETROIT NEXUS/FAST
directions: The Enrollment Center is located on the U.S. side of the Ambassador Bridge at the Fort Street Cargo Facility. Do not panic when you see the sign “no re-entry to the United States”. Most Navigation systems have not been updated for this area. The WAZE app will guide you to the facility by entering “Detroit Enrollment Center (FAST/NEXUS)” into the app. Download the WAZE app from your app store. You may also follow these directions: Step 1) Choose Your Starting Point FROM CANADA: Take the Ambassador Bridge. After the tollbooths, use the I-75 South ramp. Exit on Clark Street. Turn left on Clark Street. Turn left on Grand Blvd West. Follow the bridge to Canada sign. FROM I-75: Take the exit 47 B Bridge to Canada. Follow the bridge to Canada sign. FROM I-94: Take the exit 213 B to I-96E. Take the exit 192 B Bridge to Canada. Follow the bridge to Canada sign. FROM I-96: Take the exit 192 B Bridge to Canada. Follow the bridge to Canada sign. Step 2) Do not panic when you see the sign “No Re-Entry to the United States”. Step 3) Continue on the service route that leads to the Ambassador Bridge. Step 4) Merge left and you will see a blue sign on the left hand side of the road that says “Cargo Facility / Enrollment Center” and proceed underneath the bridge. Step 5) Under the bridge, you will find a key pad, please press button to be remotely greeted. Step 6) After you are released, approach the gate and wait for it to open. Turn right and continue to the second building on your left. Park in the designated Nexus/Fast parking area.
notes:
Thank you for scheduling your appointment at the Detroit Enrollment Center (EC),  Detroit, MI.  Please print and follow the instructions to assist you during your visit. Firearms and Weapons of any kind are not allowed anywhere within the Fort Street Cargo Facility. Due to Limited Parking, you will not be allowed in our facility more than thirty minutes in advance of your appointment time. 

 

Documents to Bring: Proof of Citizenship, Driver License, proof of employment, and any other supporting documents you believe will assist with your application, such as Certified Court Disposition for Arrest (if you were ever arrested). 

Special instructions for applicants: 

Firearms and Weapons of any kind are not allowed anywhere within the Facility. If using a Rideshare Service (Uber/Lyft) please ask your driver to wait for you until your interview is completed. Food or Drinks are not allowed in the EC. Electronic Communications Devices must be turned off. Due to limited space, event access is strictly limited to the applicant/s being interviewed (excluding minor children). Additional guest may be asked to wait in the vehicle.

For more information, go to https://ttp.cbp.dhs.gov/

directions: In Google Maps type East Port and pick first option, U.S. Customs and Border Protection Calexico East Port of Entry 1699 Carr Rd, Calexico, CA 92231.  Please follow signs to Int'l Border SENTRI/GLOBAL Office, and be careful not to go into Mexico.
notes: PLEASE MAKE SURE TO BRING WITH YOU: • Proof of income (pay-stubs, bank deposits, and income tax). • Proof of residency (mortgage statements, rental agreement, and utility bills). • Driver license, vehicle registration, and proof of insurance. • Marriage certificate, birth certificate. • School records or classes. • Machine-readable entry document such as US passport, Resident Alien Card, any other foreign passport and visa required for entry. Original documents only, No copies will be accepted. • A notarized authorization letter to enroll vehicle belonging to another person (if applicable). • If you have ever been arrested, please bring court documents verifying the disposition of the arrest (s), regardless of the date of the arrest and the outcome. HAVE ALL PERTAINABLE DOCUMENTS READY ON HAND, NOT DOING SO CAN CAUSE FOR YOUR APPLICATION TO BE DENIED OR FOR YOU TO BE RESCHEDULED. WE APPRECIATE YOUR ATTENTION TO THIS MATTER. **FAVOR ASEGÚRESE DE TRAER CONSIGO: • Comprobante de ingresos (talones de pago, depósitos bancarios e impuesto sobre la renta). • Prueba de residencia (estados de cuenta de hipoteca, contrato de alquiler y facturas de servicios públicos). • Licencia de conducir, registro del vehículo y comprobante de seguro. • Certificado de matrimonio, certificado de nacimiento. • Registros escolares o clases. • Documento de entrada legible por máquina, como pasaporte estadounidense, tarjeta de extranjero residente, cualquier otro pasaporte extranjero y visa requerida para ingresar. Solo documentos originales, no se aceptarán copias. • Una carta de autorización notariada para inscribir el vehículo perteneciente a otra persona (si corresponde). • Si alguna vez ha sido arrestado, traiga documentos judiciales que verifiquen la disposición del arresto (s), independientemente de la fecha del arresto y el resultado. TENGA LOS DOCUMENTOS PERTINENTES A LA MANO, NO HACERLO PUEDE CAUSAR QUE SU SOLICITUD SEA DENEGADA O SU CITA REPROGRAMADA.
